file=Brand Studio/tempo/operational/commands/tempo-commands.md · h=name: tempo-commands\ntype: operational/commands\nstatus: consolidated from trigger phrases in tempo's skill files — no new triggers invented\nassigned_agent: tempo (Brand Studio / Audio Branding)\ndate_added: 2026-07-08\n · p:=Routing reference for tempo.\n · tb=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| sound-identity \| "video music," "sound for [content]," "VO tone," "build our sonic guide" \| `/tempo-sound` \| · tb=\| usage-licensing \| "can we use this track," "license check," "add to the registry," "did anything lapse" \| `/tempo-license` \| · ### Rights before fit=No track is selectable until cleared and registered; a perfect-fit unlicensed track is a license request, not a selection.\n · ### What tempo does NOT take=- Producing the audio/video → pixel. Platform audio norms → pulse's playbooks. Legal interpretation → operator/counsel (clauses quoted, never construed hopefully). License spend approval → operator/board.\n · f:=Ambiguous → rights (may we) or fit (should we)?\n